article.headline: UTEP 68, Princeton 42
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- Jason Williams had 19 points and nine rebounds to lead Texas-El Paso to a 68-42 victory over Princeton on Tuesday in the championship game of the Sun Bowl Tournament. Williams was 6-for-6 from the free-throw line and had four assists. Omar Thomas added 17 points, four rebounds and an assist for UTEP (10-2). Judson Wallace scored 17 points and grabbed six rebounds for Princeton (6-4), which made 33.3 percent of its field goals in the game. The game featured three ties and six lead changes, though UTEP held Princeton to just 17 second-half points. The Miners scored 26 points off 16 Princeton turnovers and out-rebounded the Tigers 29-20.
